Date: Sat, 11 Jul 2026 18:06:21 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: close conductor write hole, noindex private reveals,
 drop edge on AI routes
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Three urgent hardening fixes (review items C2, C1, H5).

C2 — /api/conductor could overwrite "immutable" moments (security):
- The unauthenticated conductor forwarded untyped input to any registered
  agent, including the KV-writing archive-moment/remember-profile, and
  putMoment did an unconditional SET — so an anonymous POST could inject
  or clobber any published moment.
- Classify write agents as MUTATING_AGENT_NAMES and refuse them at the
  conductor with 403; they run only inside server-side workflows.
- Make putMoment write-once via a new atomic kv.setNX (Redis SET .. NX);
  an existing id is never overwritten (reported as linkActive=false).

C1 — private reveal pages were indexable (privacy leak):
- /r/[id] now exports robots noindex/nofollow, overriding the site-wide
  index:true default so recipient names/messages can't surface in search.
- robots.ts disallows /r/, /create/preview and /api/ (covers the client
  pages that can't export metadata).
- Remove the root-layout canonical:'/' that propagated to every
  metadata-less route; the homepage now declares its own canonical.

H5 — AI routes bundled the Anthropic SDK on edge (deploy risk):
- Drop runtime='edge' from compose, reflect, follow-up, plan and
  conductor; their agent graph pulls in @anthropic-ai/sdk, which pushes
  the edge bundle past Vercel's 1 MB limit (the same failure already
  fixed on /r/[id]). They now run on Node serverless.

Verified: tsc --noEmit clean, eslint 0 errors, next build green
(/r/[id] and the AI routes compile as Node dynamic; robots.txt emits
the disallow rules).

